review_blob: a sweet and mildly fruity ale. suttle taste of carmel hidden within the bitterness of the hops. a delightful brew from the fellas at Victory
dark in color with a very smooth and chocolaty flavor. has a dry after taste and almost no head
Was very impressed with this Imperial Stout, found to be the top accessible beer on some peoples lists, while i agree the full flavor rnks it high i wouldnt go as far as to rate it as number 1
Its a decent summer beer, a step up from a Bud or Corona, but not a big step
